The Zamfara State Governor, Hon. Bello Mohammed Matawalle has expressed sadness following the death of the Emir of Kaura-Namoda in Zamfara, Alhaji Ahmad Asha who died due to coronavirus complications. Recall that the monarch died on Sunday after being isolated at the Yariman Bakura Specialist Hospital, Gusau. The Emir’s blood sample was taken to Abuja for test, having been suspected of contracting COVID-19, The sample of the late monarch, returned positive. Reacting, Matawalle on Monday said Asha was a true statesman. He tweeted, “@I’m deeply saddened by the death of HRH Alh. Muhd Asha, Emir of K/Namoda earlier today. “He was a true statesman who served with distinction. “On behalf of Zamfara people, my family and I wish to convey our prayers to his departed soul and our deepest sympathy to the royal family.” Source •Late Emir of Kaura Namoda, Ahmad Muhammad Asha GUSAU - The Emir of Kaura Namoda, Ahmad Muhammad Asha also known as Sarkin Kiyawan Kaura Namoda, has died in the early hours of Sunday at the age of 71. His  younger brother,  Abdulkarim Ahmad Asha, the Dan Jekan  Kaura Namoda told… May 3, 2020 In "News" By Ishaq Zaki Kaura Namoda (Zamfara) - The Speaker of the Zamfara State House Assembly, Alhaji Sanusi Rikiji, on Friday said no fewer than 50 persons including members of Civilian Joint Task Force (CJTF) were killed in Zamfara on Tuesday. Rikiji, who revealed this during a condolence visit to Kaura Namoda… April 5, 2019 In "News" By Ishaq Zaki Kaura-Namoda (Zamfara) -  Gov. Abdulaziz Yari has directed the 17 emirs in Zamfara to immediately file detailed reports on the security situation in their domain. The governor said on Monday while receiving Sallah homage from the emirs of Kaura-Namoda, Birnin-Magaji and Zurmi, that the emirs should immediately… June 18, 2018 In "News"